"If nothing else the Internet outage that afflicted India and much of the Middle East around the Chinese New Year showed that while being unprepared for disaster is part of the human condition, some people fare a lot better than others. This applied equally from individuals to the largest corporations and even countries. But above all it revealed how dependent enterprises are, big and small, on the Internet for all aspects of working and social life, and particularly among the booming and emerging economies of the Middle East and Subcontinent."
